# Goal Description
Add a "Security" dropdown to the HR Dashboard sidebar containing links to "User", "Role", and "Permission" management. 
Implement full CRUD for [User](file:///c:/Users/afif/Downloads/Projects/Mir-HR-Management-System/app/Models/User.php#10-57), [Role](file:///c:/Users/afif/Downloads/Projects/Mir-HR-Management-System/app/Models/Role.php#8-27), and [Permission](file:///c:/Users/afif/Downloads/Projects/Mir-HR-Management-System/app/Models/Permission.php#8-22) models. 
Implement dynamic sidebar navigation based on user permissions.

## Proposed Changes

### Views & Layout
#### [MODIFY] resources/views/hr-dashboard.blade.php
- **Changes**: 
  - Change the single "Security" link into a Bootstrap dropdown (using JavaScript or CSS hover) or a collapsible menu containing "User", "Role", and "Permission".
  - Refactor sidebar items to only show if the user's role has the corresponding permission (e.g. check if `$user->role->permissions->contains('name', 'manage_security')`).

### Controllers
#### [NEW] app/Http/Controllers/UserController.php
- **Changes**: Implement [index](file:///c:/Users/afif/Downloads/Projects/Mir-HR-Management-System/app/Http/Controllers/EmployeeDashboardController.php#10-27), [create](file:///c:/Users/afif/Downloads/Projects/Mir-HR-Management-System/app/Http/Controllers/Auth/AuthenticatedSessionController.php#14-21), [store](file:///c:/Users/afif/Downloads/Projects/Mir-HR-Management-System/app/Http/Controllers/Auth/AuthenticatedSessionController.php#22-38), `edit`, `update`, [destroy](file:///c:/Users/afif/Downloads/Projects/Mir-HR-Management-System/app/Http/Controllers/Auth/AuthenticatedSessionController.php#39-52) to manage users and their details.

#### [NEW] app/Http/Controllers/RoleController.php
- **Changes**: Implement CRUD for Roles. In the [create](file:///c:/Users/afif/Downloads/Projects/Mir-HR-Management-System/app/Http/Controllers/Auth/AuthenticatedSessionController.php#14-21) and `edit` forms, list all available permissions using checkboxes so the admin can assign permissions to the role.

#### [NEW] app/Http/Controllers/PermissionController.php
- **Changes**: Implement CRUD for Permissions. Admin will be able to define names like `view_personnel`, `manage_payroll`, etc., which will represent menu options.

### Routes
#### [MODIFY] routes/web.php
- **Changes**: Add grouped routes for `/users`, `/roles`, `/permissions` using the respective resource controllers, protected by the `auth` middleware and an authorization check ensuring only users with the `HR Admin` role or `manage_security` permission can access them.

### CRUD Views
#### [NEW] resources/views/security/users/index.blade.php, create.blade.php, edit.blade.php
#### [NEW] resources/views/security/roles/index.blade.php, create.blade.php, edit.blade.php
#### [NEW] resources/views/security/permissions/index.blade.php, create.blade.php, edit.blade.php
- **Changes**: Create styled forms and tables utilizing the custom HR Dashboard aesthetics (e.g., `.hr-panel`, `.hr-table`). 
  
## Verification Plan
1. Ensure HR Dashboard sidebar "Security" acts as a dropdown or collapsible block.
2. Manually test User creation (select a role).
3. Test Role creation (select permissions).
4. Test Permission creation.
5. Verify that sidebar options in `hr-dashboard` correctly rely on these permissions to hide/show themselves.
